      "Indeed, I think the closest the canonical syntax can get to \r\n\r\n```pseudo\r\ngetMe(r.getThis().transformThat()).then(function(theStuff){\r\n    //do the thing with theStuff\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\n...the better it will be.\r\n\r\nHowever...\r\n\r\n```pseudo\r\ngetMe(function(db){ return db.getThis().transformThat(); }).then(function(theStuff){\r\n    //do the thing with theStuff\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\n...does provide a function closure for the construction of more complex statements, which could otherwise be a pain to see as a single query chain argument."
